<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans" COLOR="#400000">Originally posted by Mallissin on 09-20-1999 04:28 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">It was simply an idea I had while thinking about the allegiance system. It wouldn't be too hard to impliment, and it would help with the policing issues which plagued previous online games. It also had it's own roleplayability, of course. Too much work then what's needed I guess, after hearing your replies.

Also had in mind, a concept thrust apon me by an advocate, that they were going to allow allegiance wars. Deputies would be the only way to keep the towns safe from the battles spilling into the streets, so to speak. And the thought of a town divided between monarchs, posed a very interesting roleplaying situation (Varona of "Romeo and Juliet" with the two families). Battle to get a mayor into office that's under their control. Then have the deputies on their side, and force the other monarch out. Political wars are just as fun as the physical ones.. ;)</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
